Author: younggaruda1945
Content: As a Indonesian student studying overseas, you might be surprise that the majority of Indonesian student population are not just wealthy and affluent, but the majority of them are Chindo, mainly for undergraduate program, but for graduate it is kind off diverse, with more leaning toward Chindo student population. The majority of  "Pribumi" student are anak beaswisa and they in the graduate program, especially they are coming from wealthy and affluent background. Based on my experience, anak beaswisa are often are out-of-touch from the univeristy culture. As muslim "pribumi" studying overseas, there is dozen of myths that the average Indonesian do not know about studying overseas, ranging from program all to the the university culture. Btw, I am undergraduate students and anak sultan. Ask me guys!

Author: ataman_erkin
Content: Here, if you are a male uni student, reaching an age for military service, you obliged to do it no matter what. But, the good thing is, since every uni has military faculty, what you need to do is, showing up in the classes like usual with your peers. But, you need to go with military uniform, do classes as usual and when you finish your classes, go to military faculty and do army drills. For example, circling whole university complex with Ak on your shoulder.

Author: ataman_erkin
Content: Which for some, is still better rather then being sent somewhere to military barrack in random places
